## Phase 4: Device-Adaptive UI

#### [NEW] [PlatformUIController.cs](file:///d:/GameTopDown/GameTopDown/Assets/Scripts/Manager/PlatformUIController.cs)

Detect device → toggle mobile-only controls:

```csharp
public class PlatformUIController : MonoBehaviour
{
    [SerializeField] private GameObject[] mobileOnlyElements;
    [SerializeField] private GameObject[] desktopOnlyElements;

    public static bool IsMobile { get; private set; }

    private void Awake()
    {
#if UNITY_EDITOR
        IsMobile = UnityEditor.EditorUserBuildSettings.activeBuildTarget
            is UnityEditor.BuildTarget.Android
            or UnityEditor.BuildTarget.iOS;
#else
        IsMobile = Application.isMobilePlatform;
#endif
        ApplyPlatformUI();
    }

    private void ApplyPlatformUI()
    {
        foreach (var el in mobileOnlyElements)
            if (el != null) el.SetActive(IsMobile);
        foreach (var el in desktopOnlyElements)
            if (el != null) el.SetActive(!IsMobile);
    }

    public void OverridePlatform(bool forceMobile)
    {
        IsMobile = forceMobile;
        ApplyPlatformUI();
    }
}
```

**Mobile-only elements** (kéo vào Inspector):
- `MoveButton` (JoyStick)
- `FireButton`
- `UseSkillButton`
- `ChangeWeaponButton`

#### [MODIFY] [MenuManager.cs](file:///d:/GameTopDown/GameTopDown/Assets/Scripts/Manager/MenuManager.cs)

[EnableMovement()](file:///d:/GameTopDown/GameTopDown/Assets/Scripts/Manager/MenuManager.cs#74-94) — bỏ bật mobile buttons (do `PlatformUIController` quản lý):

